Now re-reading the question, I think I may have misunderstood it. I'm suggesting we add an `enum` to `ignition::msgs::BatteryState` so it is reachable from code. [Here](#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-msgs/src/9e06fd7f07dc7b57c0c7e455d39446f1d390b54e/proto/ignition/msgs/visual.proto#lines-47)'s an example. Something like this:

~~~
message BatteryState
{
  enum PowerSupplyStatus
  {
    UNKNOWN    = 0;
    ...
  }
  ...
}
~~~

Then from C++ this becomes `ignition::msgs::BatteryState::PoweSupplyStatus::UNKNOWN`
